## Tips &  Tricks

echo "Welcome `uname -n`! Today: `date`"

find yerine fd çalış.

Örn : fd -e php index -E Docs  # Docs klasöründe index isimli php dosyalarını ara

[RG Cheat Sheet](https://cheatography.com/njones/cheat-sheets/ripgrep/)

Search the contents of .html and .css files only for the word foobar using the Type flag (t).
$ rg -thtml -tcss foobar

Or return everything but css files using the Type Not flag (T):
$ rg -Tjs foobar

Returns a list of all .css files
$ rg -g *.css --files

* En çok yer kaplayanlar - $ du -hsx * | sort -rh | head -5
* Aktif çalışanlar  - $ systemctl list-units --type=service --state=running
* ffmpeg ile screencast - $ ffmpeg -y -f alsa -i hw:0 -video_size 1920x1080 -framerate 30 -f x11grab -i :0.0 -c:v libx264 -crf 0 -preset ultrafast output.mkv
* video size düşürme $ ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -vcodec libx265 -crf 20 output.mp4
* convert image.jpg -sampling-factor 4:2:0 -strip -quality 85 -interlace JPEG -colorspace RGB image_converted.jpg
* youtube-dl --extract-audio --audio-format mp3  "youtube url"
* Resolvconf https://wiki.manjaro.org/index.php?title=Networking
* Video Birleştirme - $ ffmpeg -i concat:"input1.mp4|input2.mp4" output.mp4


### Video Editing

- [How to use ffmpeg to combine multiple videos to one](https://ma.ttias.be/use-ffmpeg-combine-multiple-videos/)
- [How to merge multiple (more than two) videos](https://askubuntu.com/questions/637074/how-to-merge-multiple-more-than-two-videos-on-ubuntu)
- https://superuser.com/questions/510985/how-can-i-crop-a-video-to-a-part-of-the-view
- [Cut with Avidemux](https://help.presentations2go.eu/editing/CutwithAvidemux.html)

Merge two video clips into one, placing them next to each other

ffmpeg \
  -i 1.mp4 \
  -i 2.mp4 \
  -filter_complex '[0:v]pad=iw*2:ih[int];[int][1:v]overlay=W/2:0[vid]' \
  -map [vid] \
  -c:v libx264 \
  -crf 23 \
  -preset veryfast \
  output.mp4

Yan yana ve soldakinin audio dosyası

  ffmpeg \
-i "1.mp4" \
-i "2.mp4" \
-filter_complex " \
nullsrc=size=1900x950 [base]; \
[0:v] setpts=PTS-STARTPTS, scale=950x950 [left]; \
[1:v] setpts=PTS-STARTPTS, scale=950x950 [right]; \
[base][left] overlay=shortest=1 [tmp1]; \
[tmp1][right] overlay=shortest=1:x=950 \
" \
-c:v libx264 output2.mp4

